<item>
            <title>[ELY-688] Elytron Properties realm parses password with &quot;=&quot; incorrectly</title>
                <link>https://issues.jboss.org/browse/ELY-688</link>
                <project id="12315320" key="ELY">WildFly Elytron</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In case when Elytron properties-realm uses plain-text properties file and password includes &lt;tt&gt;=&lt;/tt&gt; sign then username/password is parsing incorrectly. In case when properties file contains line as &lt;tt&gt;A=B=C&lt;/tt&gt; then Elytron parses it as user &lt;tt&gt;A=B&lt;/tt&gt; with password &lt;tt&gt;C&lt;/tt&gt;. Correct behavior should be user &lt;tt&gt;A&lt;/tt&gt; with password &lt;tt&gt;B=C&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
